{"lemma":"رُكّابٌ","slug":"رُكّابٌ","root":"ر.ك.ب","root_slug":"ر-ك-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ك-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رُكّابٌ","root":"ركب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16466","n16472"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%83%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"passenger, rider"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"driver"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mountain summit"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of رَكِبَ (rakiba, “to ride”)."},"ipa":["/raː.kib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16466","headword_ar":"رِكَابٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Travelling-camels, used for riding;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which people journey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTiY~N","text_ar":"مَطِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels fit for carrying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 22:) it has no proper sing.: (S:) the word used for the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHilapN","text_ar":"رَاحِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) or, as ISh says, in the “ Book of Camels, ”"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikaAbN","text_ar":"رِكَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyrN","text_ar":"عِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels that go forth for corn"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAm","text_ar":"طَعَام"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be brought back upon them, both when they go forth and after they have come back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the former term is applied also to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels upon which people journey to Mekkeh, on which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAmil","text_ar":"مَحَامِل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are borne:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hired"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels that carry the goods and corn of merchants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but camels are not called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":", though bearing corn, [unless] if hired: [I insert"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1144},{"kind":"text","text":"the words “ or other ” and “ unless ” because it is further said,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":"are not those that bring corn for their owners; but these are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikaAbN","text_ar":"رِكَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukubN","text_ar":"رُكُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) accord. to A'Obeyd, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikaAbaAtN","text_ar":"رِكَابَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakaAy^ibu","text_ar":"رَكَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or, accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukubN","text_ar":"رُكُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikaAbN","text_ar":"رِكَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and others say that it is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakuwbN","text_ar":"رَكُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying any beast"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on which one rides,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an epithet] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) but called by ISd a subst.; (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazuwzN","text_ar":"جَزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakuwbapN","text_ar":"رَكُوبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a more special term than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakuwbN","text_ar":"رَكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in the present art.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikaAbu Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"رِكَابُ السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bearers of the clouds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the winds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) Umeiyeh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tarad~adu waAlr~iyaAHu lahaA rikaAbu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(referring to a cloud)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes to and fro"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarad~ad","text_ar":"تَرَدَّد"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tatarad~adu","text_ar":"تَتَرَدَّدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the winds being its bearers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  Also [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stirrup"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse's saddle;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known appertenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse's saddle; (S;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"same with respect to a horse's saddle as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garoz","text_ar":"غَرْز"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to a camel's:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukubN","text_ar":"رُكُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Msb","L"]},{"entry_id":"n16472","headword_ar":"رَكَّابٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakuwbN","text_ar":"رَكُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man, (K, TA,) the latter on the authority of Th, (TA,) signify the same, (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who rides much; a great rider:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rak~aAbapN","text_ar":"رَكَّابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a woman. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rak~aAbN liloA^umuwri","text_ar":"رَكَّابٌ لِلْاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who surmounts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"masters, affairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who often does so;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accustomed to embark in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertake,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to surmount,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master, them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who often embarks in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertakes, them, and therefore surmounts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"masters, them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by his knowledge, and repeated experience, and good judgment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TlE","text_ar":"طلع"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}